    "attributes": {
        "action": "Call for Overhaul & Reform of the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency & its Role",
        "additional_details": "Introduce\r\n-Learners taught by family/friend to have a minimum no. of proven lessons with an Approved Driving Instructor prior to driving test\r\n-DVSA driving test examiners to have a minimum 3 yrs ADI experience & 5 yrs to conduct Part 2/3 tests\r\n-ADIs standard to be based on pupil pass rates, if they fall below a national average for 2 yrs they take a Check test\r\n-Grant PDIs a 12 mth licence with pass rate considered for the Part 3 ADI test\r\n-ADI\u2019s to pursue complaints against the DVSA through a tribunal",
        "background": "Call for overhaul & reform of the DVSA which needs to work from reliable data/statistics when introducing reforms & changes in order to improve road safety https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/848485/road-casualties-year-ending-june-2019.pdf",
